	</head>
	<body>
		<P><FONT color="#000000" size="4"><STRONG>BCM_GETSELECTIONPOINTS</STRONG></FONT></P>
		<TABLE id="Table1" cellSpacing="3" cellPadding="0" width="100%" border="0">
			<TR>
				<TD width="100%" bgColor="#e6e6e6"><PRE>BCM_GETSELECTIONPOINTS
	wParam = 0;
	lParam = ( LPARAM )( LPRECT )pPositions;</PRE>
				</TD>
			</TR>
		</TABLE>
		<P>
			Get the start and end points of the current text selection. When there is no 
			selection all points are set to -1 and the message retursn zero. The left and 
			top fields of the RECT will describe the selection starting point and the right 
			and bottom fields the selection end point. Line and column numbers start at 1.</P>
		<UL>
			<LI>
				Returns zero on failure and non-zero on success. Failure normally indicates 
				that there is no selection.</LI></UL>
		<DL>
			<DT><EM>pPositions</EM>
				<DD>
					A pointer to a RECT structure&nbsp;in which the&nbsp;selection positions are 
					stored.&nbsp;Line and column numbers start at 1 and can go upto the amount of 
					lines in the text or the&nbsp;length of the line on which the markers are 
					currently set.</DD></DL>
		<P>NOTE: The column position is the view position. This means that with a tab size of 8 
			the columns covered by a tab are upto 8 column positions.</P>
	</body>
</html>
